<plot>A profile of sculptor Augustus Saint-Gaudens (1848-1907) who came of age during the Civil War and was a leading figure in the rebirth of American art that took place in the closing decades of the 19th Century. This documentary draws on photographs, letters, literary documents and the artist's works to create a beautiful and informative portrait of a neglected giant of American art.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?051349</url></doc>
